Sections 3.3 and 3.3.1: In sections 3.3 and 3.3.1 the element Te was inad- vertently written as the element Se which is the topic of the following sections 3.3.2 and 3.3.3. Authors thank Professor A Brinkman (University of Twente, The Netherlands) for the notification.
We searched for available experimental results for other junctions involving ultra-thin conductors which might exhibit the presence of two superconducting bands.
Topological insulators are a possible example since any supercurrent will only be transported on the surface.
The two-dimensional nature of the superconducting state in junctions based on Bi 2 Te 3 was confirmed by He et al .
Our fit to equation (3) is shown figure 8, and it reveals parameters in the expected range.
